Kiswahili is gaining much recognition worldwide.South Africa introduced it in schools early last year. In his article, “Kiswahili in PhD writing ‘tricky’” (DN, Dec. 29, 2020), Solomon Lumasia’s major point was that the main language of instruction in our education system is English, and, consequently, most people were much at ease transacting their business, specifically writing, in it.
He further opined that English is globally accepted and, hence, any deviation would make one a pariah. 



