However, whereas universities use Kiswahili as the language of instruction in its studies, they are largely beholden to linguistics books written in English. 
Kiswahili is gaining much recognition worldwide. South Africa introduced it in schools early last year.
With over 100 million speakers in Africa, and being one of the official languages of the AU, ignore it at your peril. We can easily excel in the language.
Mr Osabwa is a lecturer at Alupe University College. wosabwa680@gmail.com. In his new year’s message to the country, the President called for a renewal of minds in the New Year 2021. He paraded the newly elected Msambweni MP Feisal Bader as the “firstborn” of the so called Hustler's Movement. Ever since Abiy Ahmed came to power, the Tigray regional government has been at odds with the central government.